==English==

===Etymology===
{{bor|en|es|gringo}}, from {{m|es|griego||Greek}}, used for anyone who spoke an unintelligible language.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɡɹɪŋɡəʊ/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ɪŋɡəʊ|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|gringoes}}

# {{lb|en|slang|often|pejorative|in Latin America}} a white person from an English-speaking country.

====Related terms====
* {{l|en|gringa}} {{qualifier|female}}

